Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools include Reports and Dashboards, Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards, CRM Analytics, Get Started Using CRM Analytics, Go Mobile with CRM Analytics, Set Up the CRM Analytics Platform, Integrate Data into CRM Analytics Datasets.

Data Manager allows you to Get Started with Data Integration, Connect and Sync Your Data to CRM Analytics, Clean, Transform, and Load Data with Data Prep, Manage Recipes, Run Data Sync and Recipes to Create and Refresh Datasets.

Other Ways to Integrate Data include Get Started Faster with Data Templates, Data Template Features, Create Data Assets from a Data Template, Available Data Templates, Manage Datasets, Data Integration Best Practices, Data Integration Troubleshooting.

Gain Insights on Data Directly at Source by Explore and Visualize Your Data in CRM Analytics, Build CRM Analytics Dashboards, Embed and Customize CRM Analytics, Create and Share CRM Analytics Apps to Give Business Users a Big experience.

Develop with CRM Analytics includes Intelligent Analytics Apps, Tableau, Unified Analytics Experiences, Einstein Discovery.

Create Data Assets from a Data Template:

1. From the App Launcher, open the Data Manager.
2. Select the Data Template tab and choose a template.
3. Name your data app, add a description, and click Create.
4. View the jobs run for the data assets in the Monitor tab, and view and schedule the Data Prep recipes created by the template on the Recipes tab.

Data apps show up on the Apps tab in Analytics Studio, where users with manage access can delete apps, removing all data assets created from the template.
title: Creating Data Assets from Templates
